# Code Style

By default, follow the language's best practices. Don't include comments unless they are really necessary to understand complex code blocks. Avoid TODOs and FIXMEs in code. Avoid adding comments and docstrings in general — it's better to write clear code; add some only if it's really confusing to the reader. Remove all indentation on empty lines, and always have a blank line at the end of the file.
